Class Library

java.lang.Object
Library
public class Library
extends java.lang.Object
A library to be used by the GUI class. This Class stores books in the library, and manages loaning, returning, creation and deletion of books.
Version:
(0.5)
Author:
(Espen Otlo)

  • Method Details

    • loadLib

      public boolean loadLib()
      adds a selection of example books to the library.
      Returns:
      returns an empty string when run for the first time, or error message if the demo has been loaded previously.

    • addBook

      public boolean addBook​(java.lang.String title, java.lang.String author, java.lang.String publisher, int yearOfRelease, int numberOfPages, java.lang.String barCode)
      Creates a new book and adds it to the library if no book with matching barcode already there. Returns true if the book was successfully added, or false if a book with identical barcode exists in the library.
      Parameters:
      title - the title of the book
      author - the author of the book
      publisher - the publisher of the book
      yearOfRelease - the book's year of release
      numberOfPages - the book's number of pages
      barCode - the bar code of the book
      Returns:
      true if book was successfully added, false if duplicate was found.

    • getBookByTitle

      public Book getBookByTitle​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for a book with the given title, and returns it if found. If no books are found, returns null.
      Parameters:
      searchString - the title of the desired book
      Returns:
      Book with title matching searchString, null if no book matched the searchString

    • getBookByIndex

      public Book getBookByIndex​(int searchInt)
      Searches the library for a book with the given index number, and returns it if found. If no books are found, returns null.
      Parameters:
      searchInt - the index of the desired book
      Returns:
      Book at the given index, null if no book was at given index

    • removeByTitle

      public boolean removeByTitle​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for a book with the given title, and removes it if found. Returns true if deletion is successful, or false if no book with matching title is found.
      Parameters:
      searchString - the title to be deleted
      Returns:
      true if successful, false if no book matches the searchString.

    • removeByIndex

      public boolean removeByIndex​(int searchInt)
      Deletes book with the given index if present. Returns true if deletion was successful, or false if given index is invalid.
      Parameters:
      searchInt - the index of the book to be deleted.
      Returns:
      true if successful, false if no book with given index exists

    • searchTitle

      public java.util.ArrayList<Book> searchTitle​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for a book with given title. Returns matching hits as an ArrayList.
      Parameters:
      searchString - Partial or full title of the book to be searched for.
      Returns:
      an ArrayList containing the books with at least a partial matching title to the search String.

    • searchAuthor

      public java.util.ArrayList<Book> searchAuthor​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for books by given author. Returns matching hits as an ArrayList.
      Parameters:
      searchString - Partial or full title of the book to be searched for.
      Returns:
      an ArrayList containing the books with at least a partial matching title to the search String.

    • searchBarCode

      public java.util.ArrayList<Book> searchBarCode​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for books with given bar code. Returns matching hits as an ArrayList.
      Parameters:
      searchString - Partial or full bar code to be searched for.
      Returns:
      an ArrayList containing the books with at least a partial matching title to the search String.

    • loanOut

      public int loanOut​(java.lang.String searchString, java.lang.String loanedTo)
      Searches the library for given title and loans it out to given person if the book is available. Returns 1 if successful, 2 if book was already on loan, or 0 if no books match given title.
      Parameters:
      searchString - the title of the book to be loaned out
      Returns:
      1 if book was successfully loaned out, 2 if book was already loaned out, 3 if no book matched the search title.

    • returnBook

      public int returnBook​(java.lang.String searchString)
      Searches the library for given title and returns it if it was on loan. Returns 1 if successful, 2 if book was already in stock, or 0 if no books match given title.
      Parameters:
      searchString - the title of the book to be returned to library
      Returns:
      String containing a confirmation message if successful, or error message if failed or cancelled.

    • getBookList

      public java.lang.String getBookList()
      Sorts all the books in the library by author and title, and returns a a String list containing the index and title of all books.
      Returns:
      String listing all the books in the library by index and title.
